SIMPLE: oestrus
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: oestrus
<hw>oes"trus</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L., a gadfly;
also, frenzy, fr. Gr. <?/ gadfly; hence, sting, fury, insane desire,
frenzy.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <fld>(Zool.)</fld> <def>A genus of gadflies.
The species which deposits its larvae in the nasal cavities of sheep is
<spn>oestrus ovis</spn>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A vehement desire.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <specif>Specifically:</specif> <fld>(Physiol.)</fld>
<def>The periodical sexual impulse of animals; the period during which
female animals are most receptive to males; heat; rut.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source> <source>+PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Of</ent>⟦br⟧
